<div class="reportSection">
  <h4>Report Sections</h4>
  <p>Use report sections to group information into meaningful categories</p>
</div>

<div class="reportSection">
  <h4>D3 Visualizations</h4>
  <ul class="nav nav-pills" id="tabs2">
    <li class="active"><a href="#chart">Chart</a></li>
    <li><a href="#dataTable">Table</a></li>
  </ul>
  <div class="tab-content">
    <div class="tab-pane active" id="chart">
      <!--[if IE 8]>
      <p class="unsupported">
      This visualization is not compatible with Internet Explorer 8. 
      Please upgrade your browser, or view results in the table tab.
      </p>      
      <![endif]-->
      <p>
        See <code>src/scripts/demo.coffee</code> for an example of how to 
        use d3.js to render visualizations. Provide a table-based view
        and use conditional comments to provide a fallback for IE8 users.
        <br>
        <a href="http://twitter.github.io/bootstrap/2.3.2/">Bootstrap 2.x</a>
        is loaded within SeaSketch so you can use it to create tabs and other 
        interface components. jQuery and underscore are also available.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="tab-pane" id="dataTable">
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr>
            <th>index</th>
            <th>value</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          {{#chartData}}
          <tr><td>{{index}}</td><td>{{value}}</td></tr>
          {{/chartData}}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="reportSection emphasis">
  <h4>Emphasis</h4>
  <p>Give report sections an <code>emphasis</code> class to highlight important information.</p>
</div>

<div class="reportSection warning">
  <h4>Warning</h4>
  <p>Or <code>warn</code> of potential problems.</p>
</div>

<div class="reportSection danger">
  <h4>Danger</h4>
  <p><code>danger</code> can also be used... sparingly.</p>
</div>